51:53.376 --> 51:56.243
And of course, the book.

51:57.280 --> 51:59.680
But I am the curator, so I just walk in

51:59.749 --> 52:02.115
and I pinch the copy girl's <i>babouche.</i>

52:02.252 --> 52:05.688
I slip the book into my briefcase, and I leave.

52:07.524 --> 52:10.584
About 2:00 tomorrow, say?

52:17.667 --> 52:19.567
It is you who I do business with, <i>oui?</i>

52:20.704 --> 52:22.137
Right.

52:24.040 --> 52:27.134
Oh, right.

52:30.814 --> 52:33.146
Your smile is the sun, <i>ma chère.</i>

52:35.385 --> 52:38.718
And fallen men, we need the sun.

54:16.332 --> 54:20.098
Diamond Dog, carrying a cup and a cane.

54:21.971 --> 54:23.404
Bloom.

54:24.841 --> 54:27.207
Bloom, Bloom, Bloom.

54:30.179 --> 54:31.976
How long has it been?

54:33.082 --> 54:34.071
Mmm?

54:34.584 --> 54:36.051
Tea.

54:37.053 --> 54:39.954
Can you believe it? Tea.

54:41.624 --> 54:43.091
Been a long time, huh?

54:43.159 --> 54:45.184
If I call Stephen down here, he'll kill you.

54:45.261 --> 54:49.095
You're terrified, huh? Don't be scared.

54:49.866 --> 54:51.390
I'm an old man

54:53.369 --> 54:55.929
with no depth perception.

54:56.005 --> 54:58.473
You don't have to be scared of me.

55:01.944 --> 55:03.935
You know, it's been a funny thing,

55:04.013 --> 55:09.178
watching you boys take
what I taught you and eclipse me.

55:09.552 --> 55:11.349
I am so proud

55:11.921 --> 55:16.688
to be a footnote
in the life of the brothers Bloom.

55:16.759 --> 55:17.919
But you

55:19.729 --> 55:21.424
hate me.

55:25.535 --> 55:30.302
You probably won't believe,
but I loved you both very much.

55:31.274 --> 55:33.003
But love...

55:35.878 --> 55:38.176
You know, folks like us,

55:38.247 --> 55:42.149
you can always
blink and realize that it's a fiction.

55:43.252 --> 55:47.382
And like Peter walking on water
or Wile E. Coyote running off a cliff,

55:47.457 --> 55:50.187
if you look down in doubt,

55:51.294 --> 55:53.285
you will fall.

55:55.398 --> 56:00.631
That's the price of our lives,
the wax in our wings.

56:02.104 --> 56:04.664
One day, Stephen's going to fall.

56:05.408 --> 56:09.310
It may be glorious,
but he's going to fall hard,

56:09.378 --> 56:13.246
and he won't be there to tell you what to do,
to protect you.

56:13.483 --> 56:16.884
And without him, what would you do?

56:17.320 --> 56:20.619
I remember all the other boys
when I went for the belt.

56:20.690 --> 56:24.524
They would run. They would fight.
But not you.

56:24.594 --> 56:28.155
You were so passive, paralyzed.

56:28.831 --> 56:33.825
This is a warning, Bloom, and an offer.

56:34.170 --> 56:35.762
When he's gone,

56:36.806 --> 56:38.603
remember me.

56:44.080 --> 56:45.104
Oh!

56:45.181 --> 56:46.478
Stephen.

56:47.316 --> 56:49.580
We were just talking about you.

56:52.755 --> 56:54.052
Fuck you!

57:26.589 --> 57:28.682
I'm sorry I wasn't there.

57:29.325 --> 57:31.384
You can't always be there.

57:33.763 --> 57:35.628
Yeah, I guess I can't.

57:56.419 --> 57:57.579
Max!

58:02.592 --> 58:04.287
Aren't we a little early?

58:10.533 --> 58:12.899
Well, he's gone, that's for sure.

58:13.636 --> 58:15.763
Probably halfway around the world by now.

58:15.838 --> 58:18.033
Aren't you a wee bit early...

58:18.107 --> 58:20.132
I don't get it.

58:20.209 --> 58:22.336
If he was hightailing it,
why didn't he just wait eight hours

58:22.411 --> 58:24.709
until we traded the book for the million,

58:24.847 --> 58:27.145
then he'd a had some walking-around money.

58:29.518 --> 58:32.214
Oh, well, back to antiquing.

58:33.122 --> 58:34.817
Nothing lost, nothing gained.

58:34.890 --> 58:35.879
Oh.

58:41.197 --> 58:42.858
"Oh?"

58:47.603 --> 58:50.094
The check was cashed yesterday afternoon.

58:50.172 --> 58:53.403
He would have deposited it
in a Swiss account by now.

58:53.476 --> 58:55.603
I'm sorry, Pen. I'm sorry.

58:56.345 --> 58:57.812
Such a waste.

59:00.282 --> 59:04.150
Poor man. Poor Argentina man.

59:05.554 --> 59:08.318
I mean, he's never gonna
even see that book now.

59:08.391 --> 59:12.054
It's just gonna rot away in those catacombs.

59:15.598 --> 59:16.758
No.

59:16.832 --> 59:18.629
There is no book, all right.
We've been swindled.

59:18.701 --> 59:21.101
Well, maybe there is. Maybe it's real.

59:21.170 --> 59:24.537
- It's not real, it's a con.
- No.

59:24.740 --> 59:27.971
You know what? It's my money,
so I'm going to find out for sure.

59:28.044 --> 59:30.569
He gave us every piece
of information we need.

59:30.646 --> 59:33.638
Well, we'd have to clear
the administrative offices.

59:33.716 --> 59:35.513
Some sort of...

59:40.189 --> 59:41.622
Disruption.

59:52.234 --> 59:55.931
She's an artist with nitroglycerin.
It's kind of her thing.

59:56.005 --> 59:58.530
I feel like I want to know more about her.

59:58.607 --> 59:59.665
Yeah.

01:00:02.044 --> 01:00:06.276
<i>A few years back,</i>
<i>when we hit the top of our smuggling game,</i>

01:00:06.615 --> 01:00:08.446
<i>she just appeared.</i>

01:00:08.718 --> 01:00:12.085
<i>And we figure someday she'll just disappear.</i>

01:00:12.421 --> 01:00:15.015
Check out the tat on the back of her neck.

01:00:15.091 --> 01:00:17.958
It's an inky wisp of personal information.

01:00:18.527 --> 01:00:19.960
Essentially, it means,

01:00:20.029 --> 01:00:23.465
"When you're done with something,
blow it up."

01:00:33.943 --> 01:00:37.106
The smoke detector is in
these empty rooms in the east tower.

01:00:37.179 --> 01:00:39.409
We're gonna plant and set off a tiny, tiny...

01:00:41.450 --> 01:00:42.883
Tiny charge.

01:00:45.321 --> 01:00:48.757
A puff of smoke
sets off the fire alarm in the rafters.

01:00:48.824 --> 01:00:51.224
Fire drill ensues, offices empty.

01:00:51.293 --> 01:00:52.760
Excuse me.

01:00:52.962 --> 01:00:54.486
You have exactly four and a half minutes

01:00:54.563 --> 01:00:57.396
to get through the access hatch,
into the catacombs,

01:00:57.466 --> 01:01:01.027
grab the book and get out
before the fire brigade arrives.

01:01:01.103 --> 01:01:05.062
The abort code, in case we have to abort,
is "corned beef."

01:01:06.175 --> 01:01:07.802
For some reason.

01:01:07.877 --> 01:01:10.402
Okay,
so she blows this one up.

01:01:10.479 --> 01:01:12.344
This is Yueng Ling's backpack?

01:01:12.414 --> 01:01:13.711
Yeah.

01:01:16.385 --> 01:01:18.148
You know what I feel?

01:01:19.355 --> 01:01:20.788
Horny?

01:01:21.190 --> 01:01:22.623
Scared.

01:01:23.159 --> 01:01:26.390
And all my big talk, showing off all the time.

01:01:26.529 --> 01:01:29.464
But, I mean, this isn't a story,

01:01:30.499 --> 01:01:31.864
it's real.

01:01:33.536 --> 01:01:35.197
It's freaky scary.

01:01:38.440 --> 01:01:40.840
Well, as long as you focus on,

01:01:40.910 --> 01:01:43.242
you know, second left, third right.

01:03:32.721 --> 01:03:33.745
Okay.

01:03:42.197 --> 01:03:43.255
All right?

01:03:44.833 --> 01:03:45.857
Okay.

01:03:55.945 --> 01:03:58.470
You know, for the record,
I'm still against this.

01:03:58.547 --> 01:03:59.878
Why send her in alone?

01:03:59.949 --> 01:04:03.350
Because going in alone
is a very important thing to do.

01:04:04.019 --> 01:04:09.321
Listen, she's walking into
a tourism office during a fire drill

01:04:09.391 --> 01:04:13.452
and taking a phony manuscript
from a lousy crawlspace.

01:04:13.629 --> 01:04:16.962
