01:20:56.965 --> 01:21:02.335
<i>Where else on earth would you rather go?</i>

01:21:03.237 --> 01:21:08.641
<i>To a land of wonder when you go under</i>

01:21:09.577 --> 01:21:12.011
<i>Why would we want</i>

01:21:12.080 --> 01:21:17.382
<i>to come back at all?</i>

01:21:45.046 --> 01:21:46.240
Hey.

01:21:48.349 --> 01:21:49.441
How'd you find me?

01:21:49.517 --> 01:21:50.541
Bang Bang.

01:21:50.618 --> 01:21:52.210
How'd you find Bang Bang?

01:21:52.286 --> 01:21:55.813
She gave me her number
when we were in Mexico. Her cell.

01:21:56.290 --> 01:21:57.621
Bang Bang has a cell phone?

01:21:57.692 --> 01:21:58.818
Yeah.

01:21:59.727 --> 01:22:03.629
I think she's kind of selective in
who she gives her number to.

01:22:09.704 --> 01:22:11.797
Why are you here, Penelope?

01:22:14.609 --> 01:22:15.837
Okay.

01:22:18.513 --> 01:22:21.914
Well, I...

01:22:24.585 --> 01:22:26.485
I've had a lot of time, you know,

01:22:26.554 --> 01:22:28.385
to think, these past three months

01:22:28.456 --> 01:22:34.292
and I want you to seriously consider this.

01:22:51.679 --> 01:22:53.010
Go away.

01:22:54.515 --> 01:22:55.880
Go away.

01:22:59.754 --> 01:23:01.813
Everything Stephen said was true.

01:23:01.956 --> 01:23:04.015
I was just playing you as a mark.

01:23:05.560 --> 01:23:08.085
Okay? Everything between us,

01:23:10.565 --> 01:23:12.294
none of it was real.

01:23:14.235 --> 01:23:15.532
Okay.

01:23:28.583 --> 01:23:30.244
I don't believe you.

01:23:57.812 --> 01:24:01.373
<i>I let you do your monologue,</i>
<i>but you wanna know why?</i>

01:24:02.583 --> 01:24:04.551
I let her believe everything you said,

01:24:04.619 --> 01:24:06.883
so she'd never want to see me again.

01:24:07.722 --> 01:24:10.316
Get her away from all this for good.

01:24:30.511 --> 01:24:34.572
- You wanna tell me what I'm doing here?
- You knew she'd come back.

01:24:35.449 --> 01:24:38.907
What did you figure she was good for,
another million?

01:24:38.986 --> 01:24:40.817
$1.75 million.

01:24:44.692 --> 01:24:46.887
Look, of course she came back.

01:24:47.562 --> 01:24:49.757
She never got what she wanted.

01:24:51.365 --> 01:24:52.354
Neither did you.

01:24:52.433 --> 01:24:54.560
All right, look, we're gonna end this.

01:24:54.635 --> 01:24:56.569
You built us into this,
you're gonna fly us out,

01:24:56.637 --> 01:24:58.662
you're gonna end it, so she's done with this.

01:24:58.739 --> 01:25:01.469
End it all so she can't start up again.

01:25:03.711 --> 01:25:06.179
Are you sure that's what you want?

01:25:07.582 --> 01:25:08.913
I love her.

01:25:12.987 --> 01:25:15.421
I don't want to turn her into me.

01:25:42.016 --> 01:25:43.608
Well, we can't do the next job

01:25:43.684 --> 01:25:46.016
until we liquidate our assets
from the last job.

01:25:46.087 --> 01:25:48.214
Uh-uh, you've got my million
from the last job, so...

01:25:48.289 --> 01:25:51.486
That's profit, not capital,
the three of us already split that up.

01:25:51.559 --> 01:25:55.655
So, step number one
is to sell the book of hours.

01:25:55.730 --> 01:25:57.095
Ah.

01:25:57.698 --> 01:26:01.156
The one that you told me was fake, right?

01:26:01.235 --> 01:26:03.533
Actually, with all your random expertise,

01:26:03.604 --> 01:26:05.834
we couldn't risk a flat-out fake.

01:26:06.407 --> 01:26:10.400
But to get top dollar,
we'll have to sell it deep black market.

01:26:11.345 --> 01:26:14.837
And there's only one place
that's deep enough for that.

01:26:15.449 --> 01:26:16.780
Where?

01:26:25.092 --> 01:26:27.253
- Who'd you get, anyway?
- Hmm?

01:26:27.328 --> 01:26:29.193
To play the Russians.

01:26:35.369 --> 01:26:36.927
My boys.

01:26:40.041 --> 01:26:41.406
I don't understand.

01:26:41.475 --> 01:26:45.138
We're sending Penelope off into the sunset,
that's what we're doing.

01:26:45.212 --> 01:26:46.338
Why is he here?

01:26:46.414 --> 01:26:50.043
We need someone to pass
for the Russian mob to sell our fake book to.

01:26:50.117 --> 01:26:51.982
The Dog has his big store right here
in Saint Petersburg.

01:26:52.053 --> 01:26:53.748
All right, stop.

01:26:54.388 --> 01:26:56.015
I hate him, Stephen.

01:26:56.657 --> 01:26:58.887
But this isn't that.

01:26:58.959 --> 01:27:00.119
This is I don't trust him.

01:27:00.194 --> 01:27:02.162
Yeah, what's he gonna do?

01:27:02.229 --> 01:27:04.720
Steal our fake money?

01:27:04.799 --> 01:27:06.733
I have thought this through, believe me.

01:27:06.801 --> 01:27:09.099
And we can't end it without him.

01:27:12.239 --> 01:27:15.572
Trust me. It's gonna be okay.

01:27:21.582 --> 01:27:24.813
Stephen,
still the grand architect.

01:27:24.885 --> 01:27:30.755
Your symbols, red for temptation,
white for salvation.

01:27:31.158 --> 01:27:35.561
And our hero must face the Minotaur
before he escapes the maze.

01:27:35.629 --> 01:27:36.618
Uh-huh.

01:27:37.031 --> 01:27:38.965
Pickup will be at your store.

01:27:39.033 --> 01:27:41.968
Scare her,
think a movie version of the Russian mob,

01:27:42.036 --> 01:27:44.129
but don't hassle the girl.

01:27:44.205 --> 01:27:46.799
The girl? What's her name?

01:27:46.874 --> 01:27:48.865
You don't need to know her name.

01:27:51.011 --> 01:27:53.206
I know it. Penelope.

01:27:54.181 --> 01:27:56.513
I look forward to meeting the lady.

01:27:57.818 --> 01:27:59.217
All right, here we go.

01:27:59.286 --> 01:28:01.880
We got the back windshield wired to explode,

01:28:01.956 --> 01:28:04.823
and there's a large charge
underneath the hood.

01:28:04.892 --> 01:28:08.259
After the handoff with the Dog,
we drive out of town.

01:28:08.329 --> 01:28:10.422
Late that night, we stop at a gas station

01:28:10.498 --> 01:28:12.796
where our fake Russians double-cross us,

01:28:12.933 --> 01:28:15.231
and kill us all in a moonlight ambush.

01:28:15.302 --> 01:28:19.329
We all die. Bloom takes a bullet
so Penelope can escape.

01:28:20.474 --> 01:28:21.736
The end.

01:28:23.411 --> 01:28:24.537
Okay.

01:28:29.250 --> 01:28:31.275
You've been awfully quiet.

01:28:37.124 --> 01:28:39.558
I'm doing this for her, you know.

01:28:52.606 --> 01:28:54.574
Tomorrow is the big day.

01:29:32.079 --> 01:29:33.603
Get down!

01:30:47.621 --> 01:30:49.589
- Out!
- Come on, come on.

01:30:49.957 --> 01:30:51.686
Get out, get out.

01:31:02.836 --> 01:31:05.168
Bloom! Bloom.

01:31:09.543 --> 01:31:10.635
What happened?

01:31:10.711 --> 01:31:11.735
You okay?

01:31:13.314 --> 01:31:15.748
What happened? Where's Stephen?

01:31:16.684 --> 01:31:18.276
Stephen?

01:31:18.519 --> 01:31:19.850
I think...

01:31:19.920 --> 01:31:22.411
Bloom, I think they might have got him,

01:31:22.489 --> 01:31:25.458
because I think they double-crossed us
or something,

01:31:25.526 --> 01:31:29.257
because, you know,
I think they got Stephen, but...

01:31:29.330 --> 01:31:30.888
- Stephen's notebook.
- They're gonna want money

01:31:30.965 --> 01:31:33.126
so then we can get him back.

01:31:34.501 --> 01:31:36.025
Who's got him?

01:31:36.704 --> 01:31:39.537
Why, I think the Russians got him, Bloom.

01:31:48.983 --> 01:31:51.679
Stephen, God, please, what's happening?

01:31:52.386 --> 01:31:54.752
I don't know what to do, Stephen.

01:32:01.195 --> 01:32:02.526
Shit!

01:32:10.337 --> 01:32:14.831
If you know what's happening,
now would be a really good time to speak up.

01:32:24.151 --> 01:32:28.520
Oh, please. Please, not now.
I need your help here.

01:32:28.589 --> 01:32:30.750
I don't know what to do.

01:32:57.284 --> 01:32:58.512
Thanks.

01:33:17.571 --> 01:33:18.833
I can't believe it.

01:33:18.906 --> 01:33:21.670
What, that Bang Bang fell for a car bomb?

01:33:22.142 --> 01:33:23.666
Neither can I.

01:33:24.778 --> 01:33:26.245
Oh, you mean...

01:33:27.247 --> 01:33:29.579
You think maybe she faked it

01:33:29.650 --> 01:33:32.414
to make the Russians think she was dead?

01:33:33.587 --> 01:33:36.715
Bloom, what do we do now?

01:33:43.664 --> 01:33:45.256
It's a ransom note.

01:33:45.332 --> 01:33:46.890
It says they have Stephen.

01:33:46.967 --> 01:33:50.562
It says they want the money
wired to a specific account.

01:33:50.637 --> 01:33:53.902
They give a bank to do it at,
a manager to ask for.

01:33:54.241 --> 01:33:56.971
Then an address to go to
at 2:00 p.m., in two hours.

01:33:57.044 --> 01:33:58.375
Okay.

01:33:58.445 --> 01:34:02.609
Well, I'll wire the money from my account,
and we'll go get Stephen.

01:34:02.850 --> 01:34:04.317
It's a lot.

01:34:04.685 --> 01:34:06.243
I'll do it. I want to. I've got...

01:34:06.320 --> 01:34:07.617
Well, how much are they asking for?

01:34:07.688 --> 01:34:09.451
$1.75 million.

01:34:10.357 --> 01:34:11.346
Oh.

01:34:16.463 --> 01:34:17.452
Oh...

01:34:26.340 --> 01:34:29.969
No! I'm gonna kill him.
I am gonna kill him if that's what this is.

01:34:30.043 --> 01:34:32.341
If that's all that this is, I will kill him.

01:34:32.412 --> 01:34:34.141
Kill who? What are you talking about?

01:34:34.281 --> 01:34:36.044
I will kill him. I will... No!

01:34:36.550 --> 01:34:37.778
What?

01:34:41.088 --> 01:34:45.525
I've been an idiot. This could all be a con
by my brother to get me to...

01:34:46.827 --> 01:34:50.695
Oh, God, he wanted me to end it,
and he gets your money.

01:34:50.764 --> 01:34:52.391
Oh, God, I'm gonna be sick.

01:34:52.466 --> 01:34:55.367
But would he do that? To you?

01:34:57.237 --> 01:34:58.932
I don't know.

01:35:00.340 --> 01:35:02.740
Yes. Yeah, of course he would.

01:35:03.110 --> 01:35:05.840
To tell a story so well it becomes real.

01:35:06.413 --> 01:35:09.109
The perfect con. That's his whole...

01:35:10.818 --> 01:35:12.342
God damn it, that's what.

01:35:12.419 --> 01:35:14.182
You know what? We don't know.

01:35:15.489 --> 01:35:17.548
- We better transfer the money.
- Son of a...

01:35:17.624 --> 01:35:19.615
It's your brother's life.

01:35:21.128 --> 01:35:23.119
I'm gonna wire the money.

01:35:30.904 --> 01:35:32.030
Okay.

01:35:39.546 --> 01:35:41.878
I'm coming in with you.

01:35:42.316 --> 01:35:43.806
No, stay here.

01:35:45.586 --> 01:35:48.646
Going in alone is a very
important thing to do.

01:35:53.427 --> 01:35:55.019
I'm so scared.

01:35:58.599 --> 01:36:02.091
Anything I can imagine
finding in there, I'm scared of.

01:36:04.104 --> 01:36:06.572
I'm gonna be here when you come out.

01:36:43.710 --> 01:36:45.075
Stephen?

01:36:51.785 --> 01:36:53.275
Stephen?

01:36:57.090 --> 01:36:59.456
Game's up. Come on out.

01:37:03.263 --> 01:37:05.925
Come on, let's blow this one-hat town.

01:37:41.835 --> 01:37:43.769
- Stephen!
- No, Bloom.

01:37:48.542 --> 01:37:50.134
Did Penelope wire the money?

01:37:50.644 --> 01:37:51.838
Yeah.

01:37:56.750 --> 01:37:59.014
Stephen, tell me what this is.

01:37:59.086 --> 01:38:01.418
Jesus Christ, Bloom, I'm sorry.

01:38:01.488 --> 01:38:04.150
I don't need sorry. I need the truth.

01:38:06.660 --> 01:38:09.185
God damn it, Stephen.
You tell me what to do.

01:38:09.262 --> 01:38:10.991
- Get the hell out of here now!
- Tell me the truth.

01:38:11.064 --> 01:38:13.328
Is this a con or is it real?

01:38:15.268 --> 01:38:16.860
A con?

01:38:18.972 --> 01:38:20.599
It's real, Bloom.

01:38:24.478 --> 01:38:26.139
<i>Hello, Bloom.</i>

01:38:26.213 --> 01:38:28.181
God damn it, Bloom.
It's real, this is not a con.

01:38:28.248 --> 01:38:31.581
<i>Are you happy to hear</i>
<i>from your old Diamond Dog?</i>

01:38:31.651 --> 01:38:35.280
These are the Dog's men.
He's crossed us for revenge.

01:38:35.589 --> 01:38:36.988
Damn it, Bloom, run!

01:38:37.057 --> 01:38:39.787
<i>I told you Stephen would fall.</i>

01:38:40.994 --> 01:38:44.054
<i>And you? You are paralyzed,</i>

01:38:44.698 --> 01:38:48.691
<i>praying this is just</i>
<i>another one of Stephen's stories.</i>

01:38:49.236 --> 01:38:50.703
<i>Is it?</i>

01:38:51.338 --> 01:38:54.398
<i>Close your eyes now, sweet child.</i>

01:38:55.442 --> 01:38:58.639
<i>And I will tell you the truth.</i>

01:39:02.315 --> 01:39:03.373
No!

01:39:15.462 --> 01:39:16.724
Bloom!

01:39:23.236 --> 01:39:24.999
He's got another gun!

01:39:51.731 --> 01:39:53.961
Please tell me that's makeup.

01:39:54.468 --> 01:39:56.060
Please tell me that's a cackle-bladder,

01:39:56.136 --> 01:39:57.694
and you just pulled off the perfect con.

01:39:57.771 --> 01:39:59.136
Please.

01:40:25.765 --> 01:40:27.699
You said it, not me.

01:40:31.438 --> 01:40:33.497
Can I get a "wow" for this?

01:40:36.143 --> 01:40:37.269
Wow.

01:40:39.779 --> 01:40:42.247
You son of a bitch.

01:40:52.959 --> 01:40:55.052
You did it. You're done here.

01:40:55.128 --> 01:40:59.462
I want you to promise me you'll never
come back to St. Petersburg again.

01:41:08.008 --> 01:41:09.771
Tastes like tinfoil.

01:41:10.644 --> 01:41:14.205
All right, here's what I want you to do.
Bang Bang split?

01:41:14.581 --> 01:41:16.071
Yeah. Clean exit.

01:41:16.149 --> 01:41:17.173
How?

01:41:17.350 --> 01:41:18.681
Car bomb.

01:41:18.752 --> 01:41:19.844
Good.

01:41:20.120 --> 01:41:22.111
- Penelope?
- She's outside.

01:41:22.189 --> 01:41:23.781
All right, here's what.

01:41:24.858 --> 01:41:27.986
<i>Take Penelope to Helsinki,</i>
<i>get that flight to Rio.</i>

01:41:28.061 --> 01:41:30.552
<i>Play out the whole</i>
<i>"on the run from vengeful Russians" thing,</i>

01:41:30.630 --> 01:41:33.155
<i>that'll be fun for her.</i>
<i>Play it like I'm dead, actually.</i>

01:41:33.233 --> 01:41:35.326
That'll add some gravity to everything.

01:41:35.402 --> 01:41:37.529
And I'll see you when I see you.

01:41:38.572 --> 01:41:41.268
- When?
- I don't know. Not too soon, I hope.

01:41:41.341 --> 01:41:44.003
Last thing you need is me hanging around.

01:41:44.077 --> 01:41:46.739
Anyway, how am I going to top this?

01:41:47.113 --> 01:41:48.375
Bloom,

01:41:49.783 --> 01:41:51.216
pick a card.

01:41:53.320 --> 01:41:55.379
- All right.
- Got it?

01:41:55.889 --> 01:41:57.220
Yeah.

01:42:04.998 --> 01:42:07.899
That's the best card trick I've ever seen.

01:42:09.836 --> 01:42:12.202
Wish you had a bigger audience.

01:42:12.639 --> 01:42:15.369
You're the only audience I ever needed.

01:42:26.753 --> 01:42:28.118
I love you.

01:42:31.157 --> 01:42:32.283
Bye.

01:42:40.634 --> 01:42:41.862
Shh. Shh. Shh.

01:42:41.935 --> 01:42:44.130
It's okay. It's okay.

01:45:04.244 --> 01:45:07.270
You know, he said this thing to me once.

01:45:09.916 --> 01:45:12.180
He said to me,

01:45:12.252 --> 01:45:15.949
"There's no such thing as an unwritten life.

01:45:18.591 --> 01:45:20.752
"Just a badly written one."

01:45:26.699 --> 01:45:28.132
Oh, God.

01:45:31.337 --> 01:45:33.134
I love you, Bloom.

01:45:38.678 --> 01:45:40.942
You know what we're gonna do?

01:45:45.985 --> 01:45:48.180
We're gonna live

01:45:49.422 --> 01:45:52.880
like we're telling the best story
in the whole world.

01:45:58.398 --> 01:46:00.127
Are you ready?

01:46:10.310 --> 01:46:12.938
<i>And Stephen said</i>
<i>something else, once.</i>

01:46:14.113 --> 01:46:16.604
<i>"The perfect con is one</i>
<i>where everyone involved</i>

01:46:16.683 --> 01:46:19.174
<i>"gets just the thing they wanted."</i>

01:46:26.226 --> 01:46:27.557
<i>Well...</i>

01:50:22.428 --> 01:50:24.555
<i>You came to me</i>

01:50:25.064 --> 01:50:30.001
<i>In the hospital ward when I blew out my knee</i>

01:50:31.137 --> 01:50:35.597
<i>But I wasn't there to be cared for or carried</i>

01:50:39.879 --> 01:50:42.780
<i>'Cause I was asleep</i>

01:50:42.849 --> 01:50:47.877
<i>In my bed, in my house</i>
<i>at the end of our street</i>

01:50:49.021 --> 01:50:53.549
<i>While you drove across town</i>
<i>at 3:00 in the morning</i>

01:50:56.362 --> 01:50:59.923
<i>It was fake</i>

01:51:01.000 --> 01:51:04.197
<i>For the sake</i>

01:51:05.805 --> 01:51:09.366
<i>Of making you take me for real</i>

01:51:09.776 --> 01:51:16.443
<i>But I guess you're even less impressed</i>

01:51:24.123 --> 01:51:27.058
<i>If the world is a stage</i>

01:51:27.593 --> 01:51:32.758
<i>And we're all of us actors</i>
<i>in some cosmic play</i>

01:51:33.900 --> 01:51:38.894
<i>I am the man at the masquerade</i>

01:51:41.040 --> 01:51:44.237
<i>Who was fake</i>

01:51:45.711 --> 01:51:49.807
<i>For the sake</i>

01:51:50.716 --> 01:51:54.208
<i>Of making you take me for real</i>

01:51:54.754 --> 01:52:01.091
<i>But I guess you're even less impressed</i>

01:52:01.160 --> 01:52:07.827
<i>I keep trying to paint a picture</i>

01:52:09.836 --> 01:52:12.361
<i>'Cause what I drew</i>

01:52:14.240 --> 01:52:17.266
<i>Could be improved</i>

01:52:17.343 --> 01:52:20.870
<i>If I could make you see</i>

01:52:21.314 --> 01:52:26.616
<i>More flame than flicker</i>

01:52:27.086 --> 01:52:30.419
<i>These half-truths</i>

01:52:32.391 --> 01:52:36.657
<i>Could be improved</i>

01:52:36.729 --> 01:52:40.961
<i>With less of me</i>

01:52:44.503 --> 01:52:47.438
<i>And more you</i>

01:52:52.912 --> 01:52:55.972
<i>Believe what I speak</i>

01:53:04.257 --> 01:53:08.250
<i>At least just keep</i>

01:53:15.801 --> 01:53:19.259
<i>Speaking to me</i>

